Project Aletheia - α-fair, Cryptographically-Auditable Allocation Framework

Additional Terms and Clarifications:

1. RESEARCH AND ACADEMIC USE
   This software is provided for research, educational, and academic purposes.
   While commercial use is permitted under the MIT License, users are encouraged
   to cite the original work in academic publications and commercial applications.

2. CRYPTOGRAPHIC IMPLEMENTATIONS
   The cryptographic components of this software (including zero-knowledge proof
   implementations) are provided for research and educational purposes. Users
   are responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable export control laws
   and regulations in their jurisdiction.

3. FAIRNESS AND ETHICAL CONSIDERATIONS
   This software is designed to promote fairness and transparency in resource
   allocation. Users are encouraged to consider the ethical implications of
   their applications and to use the software in ways that promote social good
   and equitable outcomes.

4. THEORETICAL COMPONENTS
   The mathematical theorems, proofs, and theoretical frameworks included in
   this software are contributed to the scientific community. While the software
   implementation is licensed under MIT, the theoretical contributions are
   intended to advance scientific knowledge and may be freely used in academic
   research with appropriate citation.

5. DATA AND PRIVACY
   Users of this software are responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable
   data protection and privacy laws (including but not limited to GDPR, CCPA,
   and other regional privacy regulations) when processing personal or sensitive
   data through the allocation systems provided.

6. PATENT GRANTS
   To the extent that the copyright holders have patent rights that would
   necessarily be infringed by implementation of the algorithms and methods
   described in this software, such patent rights are licensed under the same
   terms as the software itself.

7. CONTRIBUTION LICENSING
   By contributing to this project, contributors agree that their contributions
   will be licensed under the same MIT License terms. Contributors retain
   copyright to their individual contributions while granting the project
   the right to distribute their contributions under this license.

