Community and Governance:

Project Aletheia is developed as an open-source community project. All
contributors are expected to abide by the project's Code of Conduct and
Contributing Guidelines.

The project is governed by the principle of meritocratic consensus among active
contributors, with final decision-making authority resting with the project
maintainers for matters of technical direction, quality standards, and
community management.

Contributions are welcomed from researchers, developers, and practitioners
interested in advancing fair resource allocation through rigorous mathematical
foundations and cryptographic auditability.

